we can clearly see 0 values in the columns slag and ash.¶

Count of the number of missing values on each of these columns. We can do this my marking all of the values in the subset of the DataFrame we are interested in that have zero values as True.¶

Count the number of NaN values in each column¶

Any value in a dataset that is at an abnormal distance from all other values can be termed as an outlier. Outliers generally tend to skew the mean radically.¶

Outliers can be present in the dataset with very high value or with a very low value.¶

In [25]:
np.median(feature)
Out[25]:
125.30000000000001

Its potential to skew the mean of a data set radically¶

Overall Observations¶

- Pair plot shows a clear and nice view of all variables and their realtion ship with all other variables.¶

  • Feature Distributions
  • Check each attribute by looking at box and whisker plots
  • Age attribute has an lot of outliers
  • we can clearly see 0 values in the columns slag and ash.
  • Count of the number of missing values on each of these columns. We can do this my marking all of the values in the subset of the DataFrame we are interested in that have zero values as True.
